occupation: Sales Representative, Nippon Telegraph & Telephone Global IP Network (GIN) at NTT Ltd.
headline: North America & EMEA Sales | NTT DATA Global IP Transit Network (GIN) AS2914 | Wholesale IP Transit, VLink P2P Ethernet, DDoS Protection, Subsea Cable
summary:
Pipeline and sales accelerator who quickly assesses customers' challenges, builds rapport and instills trust to generate millions in revenue across North American & EMEA markets

Extensive technology sales, marketing, and business development experience combined with an entrepreneurial spirit to out-work competitors for business success

AREAS OF EXPERTISE
B2B Software Sales | Venture Capital | SaaS Applications | Business Development | Negotiations | Sales Cycle Management | Channel Sales | Consultative Selling | Lead Generation | Market Analysis | Go-To-Market Strategy | Sales Presentations | Pipeline Management | Trade Shows | Networking | Vendor Management | Marketing | Sales Automation Tools: Outreach.io | CRM Platforms: Salesforce, Dynamics | MSFT: Word, PowerPoint, Excel

Over a decade of professional experience marketing technology products and services including managed care, clinical EMR applications, an IoT smart-building platform, and global telecom.

Proven track record in marketing disruptive solutions in startup environments to technical, clinical and C-Suite buyers. Gabe has closed deals at a seed stage company engaging with Fortune500 healthcare IDNs. He has sold to and consultatively managed commercial accounts ranging from SMB to Mid-Market to Enterprise customers across multiple industries and regions, including USA, Canada and EMEA.

Gabe is passionate about startups spanning from bootstrap, angel, seed, later-round funding stages through acquisition or IPO. He enjoys building lasting value for clients, innovating, and keeping a pulse on markets to identify attractive business opportunities for his team and investors.

experiences.title: Sales Representative, Nippon Telegraph & Telephone Global IP Network (GIN)
experiences.description:
Gabe has achieved and maintained 125% overall to quota with 11 out of 12 months post-training at or above performance target and consistently ranked #1 on an 8-member sales team.

He has generated 95 new logo opportunities representing $4.5million in ARR pipeline to date. Of these, 12 deals have closed so far totaling $320k in ARR with several others currently in late stages of the sales cycle.

NTT DATA is a global telecom leader in all Internet-related businesses. Our Tier-1 Global IP backbone, consistently ranked among the top networks worldwide, spans the Americas, Europe, Asia and Oceania, providing the best possible environment for content, data and video transport through a single autonomous system number (AS2914). 

The company’s highly reliable IP transit and DDoS protection services, along with extensive global private peering, keep our customers at the forefront of Internet technology.
 
NTT DATA brings together over 30 subsidiary companies and organizations within the NTT Group, including NTT Communications, the Global IP Network, Dimension Data, NTT Security and Pacific Crossing, among others. 

Headquartered in London UK, NTT DATA employs more than 40,000 people globally and delivers services in over 200 countries and regions. NTT DATA is part of Nippon Telegraph & Telephone, based in Japan, one of the world's largest companies in the Fortune Global 100 list of 2023.
 
For more information, please visit:
website: www.gin.ntt.net 
X: @GinNTTnet.

Tasked to help founders, CEOs, COOs, & CFOs at tech startups increase employee engagement and retention, streamline people operations, lower burn rate/extend runway, attract talent, protect valuation, and maximize the bottom line.

experiences.title: Business Development & Marketing Manager, Healthcare Division
experiences.description:
Enlighted is the leading IoT platform for smart buildings backed by leading VCs including Kleiner Perkins, Draper Fisher Jurvetson (DFJ), and Intel Capital. The company was acquired by Siemens Building Technology Division in Q2 2018.

Joined the Go-To-Market team to sell the analytics platform that provides smart energy solutions and systems across US for commercial environments. Utilized combination of sales prospecting strategies to maximize opportunities to present and consult with customers on energy cost savings, space optimization, and real-time location (RTLS) systems. Identified, qualified, and managed accounts strategically targeting hospitals and health systems nationally.

Enlighted’s mission is to help customers reach long-range sustainability goals while saving money and increasing efficiency. With a first-in-class sensor and analytics platform and multiple SaaS applications, the company provides smart energy and real-time location systems for commercial environments.

experiences.title: National Sales & Marketing Manager
experiences.description:
TransformativeMed develops and implements clinical workflow software that is embedded into the electronic medical record for busy clinicians to receive and use the most relevant data for real-time patient care decisions. Clinicians spend less time searching for data in their EMR and more time providing safe and effective care. 

A spinout of UW Medicine formed in 2012 and backed by WRF Capital, the company currently offers five best-in-class SaaS applications installed in over 200 hospitals nationally (40+ health systems, zero customer churn)

Joined company in seed stage of startup as fourth employee and earned promotion in 8 months after leading client acquisition strategy. Helped raise Series A Funding in 2017/2018 and company now has over 50 employees. 

Delivered results using hybrid approach of outside and inside sales strategies to build and nurture relationships, assist customers, and launch 4 products. Managed B2B sales process and leveraged Salesforce CRM: lead generation, prospecting, discovery/qualification, building internal champions within target accounts, sales presentations, proposals, negotiations, closing through contracting to implementation kick-off. Presented, closed, and managed 60% of corporate customer-account base.

experiences.title: Inside Sales Team Lead
experiences.description:
MCN provides the premier physician network in America whose doctors deliver impartial second opinions of treatment plans, injuries, & disabilities for payer clients that include carriers, TPAs, self-insured employers, law firms, & government funds. As a result, 20 of the top 25 US insurance carriers as well as many Fortune 500 companies (including the world's largest employer—Walmart) utilize MCN for IMEs and Peer Reviews. The company was acquired by Mitchell International in Q2 2018.

Presented and conveyed business solutions to customers throughout US. Attended tradeshows, developed leads, and identified opportunities for growth. Oversaw start-up of inside sales department with up to 8 direct reports for medical assessment services sold to payers claims departments nationwide. Recruited, hired, trained, motivated, and evaluated team as a player-coach. Acquired new business, managed multiple pipelines, grew current client accounts, and generated leads for senior account executives.
